Rep. Eric Swalwell (D., Calif.) told CNNs Wolf Blitzer on Thursday that hes rooting for President Donald Trumps negotiations with North Korea.

Swalwell, a frequent critic of Trump, was asked by Blitzer if he gives Trump credit after Secretary of State Mike Pompeo negotiated the release of three Americans captured by North Korea.

A date and location were also scheduled for Trumps summit with North Korean dictator Kim Jong Un.